40
00:02:44,106 --> 00:02:46,967
I mean, the old way, right, was that a designer would write a spec,

41
00:02:47,507 --> 00:02:49,728
the programmer would go off and implement the spec,

42
00:02:49,768 --> 00:02:51,688
he'd come back eventually and they would playtest it,

43
00:02:52,609 --> 00:02:53,609
and it might get repeated.

44
00:02:54,070 --> 00:02:55,590
Maybe. That was kind of how things worked.

45
00:02:56,071 --> 00:02:59,272
But nowadays, that's not even really how we even make games anymore.

46
00:02:59,312 --> 00:03:01,213
A lot of times a system designer will write the doc.

47
00:03:01,533 --> 00:03:03,133
The programmers will then implement a tool

48
00:03:03,714 --> 00:03:05,774
that the content designers will use to make the game.

49
00:03:06,635 --> 00:03:07,975
And then the programmers will support

50
00:03:08,676 --> 00:03:10,997
both of those designers with tool and feature changes.

51
00:03:11,737 --> 00:03:13,918
And then we keep doing that over and over again until we ship.

52
00:03:13,958 --> 00:03:16,079
And then many times we even keep doing it afterwards

53
00:03:16,119 --> 00:03:19,180
because games are online nowadays and we can update them all the time.

54
00:03:19,860 --> 00:03:21,821
Now obviously this is more of a AAA process.

55
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:25,326
and there's differences if you're doing an indie team or what have you.

56
00:03:25,627 --> 00:03:27,387
But this is kind of how games are done nowadays.

57
00:03:27,928 --> 00:03:32,490
And as you can see, there's a much tighter coupling between the designers and the programmers

58
00:03:32,550 --> 00:03:34,551
in the new system than there ever was in the old system.

59
00:03:36,112 --> 00:03:39,494
The other reason I'm doing this talk is because features themselves in our games are changing.

60
00:03:39,994 --> 00:03:46,238
You know, while the disciplines are still in the big three, you know, designers, programmers,

61
00:03:46,318 --> 00:03:48,899
artists are how we divvy out our staff.

62
00:03:50,156 --> 00:03:52,598
Game features are not really divided that way anymore.

63
00:03:52,638 --> 00:03:53,679
I mean, even this feature.

64
