Is there anybody in this room that can tease apart which was

69
00:04:08,713 --> 00:04:12,717
the programming and which was the design on this feature?

70
00:04:14,357 --> 00:04:18,258
As our games become increasingly complex, the features themselves become increasingly

71
00:04:18,338 --> 00:04:24,761
complex and they require these cross-disciplinary teams to work super tightly if they're going

72
00:04:24,781 --> 00:04:25,181
to work out.

73
00:04:26,782 --> 00:04:33,025
And these two groups can be especially tough to harmonize because they really don't think

74
00:04:33,105 --> 00:04:34,085
anything like each other.

75
00:04:36,887 --> 00:04:42,049
So the things I want to cover in this talk are basic differences between the two.

76
00:04:43,736 --> 00:04:47,859
actually working together as far as establishing a connection and ongoing sort of things.

77
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:52,463
And then some bridge methods that are starting to be used by the industry.

